The father of a boy killed in the Chardon High School shooting in Ohio died on Thursday morning at his home on the second anniversary of the rampage.

A family member found 48-year-old Russell King Sr. dead inside his home, said Lt. John Hiscox of the Geauga County Sheriff's Department.

The cause of death had not been determined, and a coroner was investigating. Hiscox said there were no signs of foul play.

