‘Whatever transpired, there's no question Russell King is another victim of this tragic shooting two years ago today,’ said Craig Bashein, an attorney who represents the family in a wrongful death lawsuit.

King's 17-year-old son, Russell King Jr., was one of three students killed in the shooting at Chardon High School east of Cleveland.

T.J. Lane opened fire in the school's cafeteria with a .22-Ruger before classes began. He also killed Daniel Parmertor, 16, and Demetrius Hewlin, 16. Russell was 17.

Three other students were wounded, including Nick Walczak, Nate Mueller and Joy Rickers.

